#encoding: utf-8

Feature: Comparison2 - Half-bounded Range

  Scenario: [1] Comparing strings and integers using > in an AND'd predicate
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (root:Root)-[:T]->(:Child {var: 0}),
             (root)-[:T]->(:Child {var: 'xx'}),
             (root)-[:T]->(:Child)
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH (:Root)-->(i:Child)
      WHERE exists(i.var) AND i.var > 'x'
      RETURN i.var
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | i.var |
      | 'xx'  |
    And no side effects

  Scenario: [2] Comparing strings and integers using > in a OR'd predicate
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (root:Root)-[:T]->(:Child {var: 0}),
             (root)-[:T]->(:Child {var: 'xx'}),
             (root)-[:T]->(:Child)
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH (:Root)-->(i:Child)
      WHERE NOT exists(i.var) OR i.var > 'x'
      RETURN i.var
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | i.var |
      | 'xx'  |
      | null  |
    And no side effects

